div1.ab: IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
In the Matter of the Application of John W. Considine for Writ of Habeas Corpus.
div1.p: And now on this 29th day of June, 1897, on reading and filing the petition of John W. Considine, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, it is hereby ordered by me as judge, that said application for a Writ of Habeas Corpus be and the same is hereby set for hearing before the United States Circuit Court for the District of Washington, at the court-room of said court, in the City of Seattle, at 10 o'clock A. M. on Tuesday, the 20th day of July, 1897.

And it is further ordered that a copy of this order be served within five (5) days from the date hereof, on John A. Pierce, Prosecuting Attorney for Spokane County, or his assistant, and upon Patrick Henry Winston, Attorney general for the State of Washington, or his assistant.
div1.ab: IN THE Circuit COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON
In re. Application of John W. Considine for Writ of Habeas Corpus
Filed June 29 1897 A Reeves Ayres Clerk. By A. N. Moore Deputy.
